  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe current implementation in namespace `quo2.foundations.shadows` has one bug and one important optimization technique that can be applied.\r\n\r\n1. The vars `normal-scale` or `inverted-scale` and `inner-shadow` are not functions. This is a bug, because their values won't change when the application theme changes between dark & light modes.\r\n2. The current implementation generates unnecessary GC pressure due to the constant re-creation of a large map and also rather expensive calls to `colors/alpha` (this function is not even memoized).\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nThere are not that many usages of `quo2.foundations.shadows`, so it's a good opportunity to rethink a little bit its API. A single function `get` could be exposed that would efficiently get (using `get-in`) the shadow values from a statically defined map of all possible shadows (dark/light modes & normal/inverted shadows). This would solve both of the problems previously described.\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n\r\n[Figma Foundations > Shadows](https://www.figma.com/file/v98g9ZiaSHYUdKWrbFg9eM/Foundations?type=design&node-id=624-752&mode=design&t=EcFQjn8F4Bukxhn0-0)",
